sections.title: Chart top 10 hosts by CPU usage

grail.canonicalQuery:
timeseries by:{dt.entity.host}, cpu = avg(dt.host.cpu.usage)
| sort arrayAvg(cpu) desc
| limit 10

sections.markdown:
## Forecasting Metrics

- In the section below we'll use CPU Metrics we've collected for the VM hosts in our lab. 
- Next we'll run the Davis Analyzer to predict how the CPU utilization of the host will be for the host.  

### Here are the instructions to predict the CPU utilization.  
 - Select the next section of the Notebook and 
 - Click on **Run Analysis** to run the DQL query and Davis Analyzer on the host metrics
 - For the timeframe select **Last 2 Hours** 
   - To view how to turn on Davis Analyzer for predictions, click on Options button, click on Davis AI at the bottom
   - On the next screen you'll notice we are using the **Forecast** Analyzer
 - On the chart you'll notice blue shading that shows above & below the line.  
   - Based on the metrics, Davis is predicting the CPU utilization to within that blue shade for this host.

grail.canonicalQuery:
timeseries by:{dt.entity.host}, avg(dt.host.disk.free)
| fields `avg(dt.host.disk.free)`, dt.entity.host, interval, timeframe

metrics.description: Percentage of free space available for user in file system. On Linux and AIX it is % of free space available for unprivileged user. It doesn't contain part of free space reserved for the root.
